<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-462-400  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 462 400.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Computer Graphics and Applications  July 1989 v9 n4 p85(10).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>The Intel i860 64-bit processor: a general-purpose CPU with 3Dgraphics capabilities. (central processing unit)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Grimes, Jack; Kohn, Les; Bharadhwaj, Rajeev.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Intel Corp's i860 general-purpose 64-bit microprocessor (MPU)includes several features and facilities for implementing low-cost3D graphics workstations.andP;  The MPU includes areduced-instruction-set computer (RISC) integer processing core,floating-point units, graphics unit, memory-management unit, dataand instruction caches, and a bus control unit.andP;  The graphics unitincludes features that provide pixel-intensity interpolation,depth interpolation, and depth buffer check.andP;  Most of the graphicsfunctionality of the i860 is implemented in complementarysoftware.andP;  The other features of the MPU that support graphicsperformance are very high speed floating-point performance, theon-chip caches, and very wide data paths.andP;  The 40 MHz i860 offers78,100 Dhrystones per second and 500,000 floating-point transformsper second performance.andP;  Details of the MPU's design aredescribed.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Intel Corp. (products).andO;Ticker:    INTC.andO;Product:   Intel 80860 (Microprocessor) (design and construction).andO;Topic:     64-BitMicroprocessorsSpecificationsGraphics Systems.andO;Feature:   illustrationcharttable.andO;Caption:   Diagram of the single-chip processor. (chart)Pixel formats for 8-, 16-, and 32-bit pixels. (chart)Six steps in the inner loop for Gouraud shading a scan line.andO;(table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>